<h2 style="text-align: center;">How To Make Sangria:</h2>
<p>Homemade sangria couldn&#8217;t be easier to make.Â  Simply&#8230;</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Chop your fruit:Â </strong>Dice the orange, lemon and green apple into evenly-sized pieces.</li>
<li><strong>Stir everything together:Â </strong>Combine the diced fruit,Â wine, brandy, the juice of one orange, and a cinnamon stick together in a large pitcher.</li>
<li><strong>(Optional) Add sweetener:Â </strong>If you prefer a sweeter sangria, feel free to add in a tablespoon or two of sweetener at a time until the sangria reaches your desired level of sweetness.</li>
<li><strong>Cover and refrigerate:Â </strong>Pop the pitcher in the fridge for at least 30 minutes or up to 4 hours before serving, in order to let those flavors meld together.</li>
<li><strong>Serve:Â </strong>Then serveÂ the sangria over ice, topping off each glass with a splash of bubbly soda (or sparkling water) if desired.</li>
</ol>
<p><img data-pin-title="Sangria" class="aligncenter wp-image-59011 size-full" title="LOVE this easy sangria recipe! It only takes 10 minutes to prep, it's customizable with whatever kind of wine or fruit you have on hand, and it's always a crowd fave. Perfect for easy summer entertaining! | gimmesomeoven.com #sangria #cocktail #drink #summer #spain #recipe" src="http://www.gimmesomeoven.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Authentic-Spanish-Sangria-Recipe-4.jpg" alt="Spanish Sangria Recipe" width="1392" height="2088" data-pin-description="LOVE this easy sangria recipe! It only takes 10 minutes to prep, it's customizable with whatever kind of wine or fruit you have on hand, and it's always a crowd fave. Perfect for easy summer entertaining! | gimmesomeoven.com #sangria #cocktail #drink #summer #spain #recipe" srcset="https://www.gimmesomeoven.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Authentic-Spanish-Sangria-Recipe-4.jpg 1392w, https://www.gimmesomeoven.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Authentic-Spanish-Sangria-Recipe-4-1100x1650.jpg 1100w, https://www.gimmesomeoven.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Authentic-Spanish-Sangria-Recipe-4-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.gimmesomeoven.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Authentic-Spanish-Sangria-Recipe-4-320x480.jpg 320w" sizes="(max-width: 1392px) 100vw, 1392px" /></p>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Sangria Recipe Variations:</h2>
<p>As I mentioned above, the beauty of sangria is that it&#8217;s really more of a method than an exact recipe.Â  So just gather whatever ingredients you have on hand and customize a batch to your liking!Â  For example, feel free to&#8230;</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Use a different wine:Â </strong>Red wine is traditional with Spanish sangria.Â  But a good Spanish white or rosÃ© wine would also work great!</li>
<li><strong>Use a different liqueur:Â </strong>If brandy isn&#8217;t your thing, cognac or orange liqueur (such as Cointreau, Grand Marnier or Triple Sec) are also popular additions to sangria here in Spain.</li>
<li><strong>Add different fruit:Â </strong>Sangria is the perfect use for leftover fresh or frozen fruit, so feel free to add in whatever you have on hand.Â  Any juicy fruits (such as citrus, berries, grapes, pineapple, mango, kiwi, etc.) would be delicious.</li>
<li><strong>Add fresh ginger:Â </strong>If you would like to give your sangria a bit of a kick, muddle in a few slices of fresh ginger.</li>
</ul>
